Boil @water{300%ml} in a medium #pot{}. When boiling, add @salt{1/4%tsp}, stir in the @rice{150%grams}, lower the heat to medium and pop on a #lid{}.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat (still covered).

Leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Cut the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets.

Place a large pan over medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once pan is hot, add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%grams} and fry until browned on all sides, turning occasionally, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Once the chicken is browned, add the onion and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

When onion has softened, add the @korma curry paste{1%sachet}, @chicken stock{1%sachet} and @water{75%ml}.

Stir to combine. Add half the @creme fraiche{62.5%grams} and stir until fully mixed.

Stir in the broccoli.

Bring to the boil and simmer until broccoli is tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Season to taste with salt, pepper, and @sugar{to taste}.

Divide the rice between plates. Top with the chicken korma curry.